The Police on Monday docked an unemployed man, Semiu Oloyede, at a Badagry Magistratesâ€™ Court for allegedly receiving a stolen Nissan Cabstar Pickup vehicle valued at N700, 000. Oloyede is facing a count charge of receiving a stolen vehicle. The Prosecutor, Insp. Clement Okumose, told the court that the accused committed the offence on Jan.15, at Black Sign Board, Magbon, in the Badagry area of Lagos. Okumose said that the defendant received one Nissan Cabstar Pickup vehicle with registration number, XT 760 KRD, valued at N700,000 from one Bolaji Olajide. He said that the stolen vehicle belonged to Opeoluwa Ogundipe, the complainant.The prosecutor said the offence contravened Section 328 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015 (Revised). The defendant, however, pleaded not guilty to the charge.The Chief Magistrate, Aka Bashorun, admitted him to bail in the sum of N50, 000 with one surety in like sum. He adjourned further hearing in the case until Dec. 11. NAN